procedures.name: Blood Sampling
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation, and pregnancy testing.

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample
procedures.description: Collection of urine for drug screening, urinalysis, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour collection for copper and molybdenum measurement.

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Stool Sample
procedures.description: Collection of fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: Includes assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems, as well as height and weight.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and clinically significant findings.

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Collection and follow-up of adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Dietary Control
procedures.label: Controlled Diet
procedures.description: Provision of copper- and molybdenum-controlled meals during inpatient periods.

procedures.name: Cannula Placement
procedures.label: IV Cannula
procedures.description: Placement of a cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

code.decode: Introduction of needle or intracatheter, vein

procedures.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometry
procedures.label: ICP-MS Analysis
procedures.description: Laboratory analysis method used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine or serum pregnancy testing for females of childbearing potential.

code.decode: Urine pregnancy test, by visual color comparison methods

procedures.name: Medical History Review
procedures.label: History Review
procedures.description: Collection of participant medical history, demographics, Wilson disease history, and prior treatments.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram System
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead ECGs for cardiac monitoring.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure and Heart Rate Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate.

medicalDevices.name: Intravenous Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula placed in a vein to allow for repeated blood draws while minimizing needle sticks.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Laboratory equipment used for elemental analysis of copper and molybdenum in biological and dietary samples.
